<InfoLayout
  title="About · StudentLancers"
  description="StudentLancers is a marketplace for college students and the companies that hire them."
  eyebrow="About"
  heading="A marketplace built for the people it serves."
  lead="StudentLancers exists because the existing options for college hiring are slow, expensive, or both. We are building the one we wish we had."
>
  <h2>Why this exists</h2>
  <p>
    Every member of the team behind StudentLancers has either hired interns
    the hard way or spent a college career chasing gigs. We know what works
    and what doesn't. The platform is shaped by that experience.
  </p>

  <h2>What we believe</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Talent is everywhere; access is not. Verified .edu enrollment levels the field.</li>
    <li>Escrow protects both sides — companies don't pay for unfinished work, students don't ship into the void.</li>
    <li>Reviews are a two-way street. Both sides earn a track record that travels with them.</li>
    <li>Honest pricing beats clever pricing. An 8% fee is straightforward.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Where we are</h2>
  <p>
    We launched in private beta in 2026. The first cohort is small — a few
    hundred verified students and a handful of design-forward companies. As
    we grow, we'll keep the same standards: every student verifies their
    enrollment, every brief gets eyes on it before it goes live.
  </p>

  <h2>How to reach us</h2>
  <p>
    We answer every email. <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a> for press,
    partnerships, careers, or to share a feature request.
  </p>
</InfoLayout>
